      • splitObj

        public splitObj​(java.awt.image.BufferedImage image,
                int[] ArrX,
                int[] ArrY,
                int multiplier,
                splitObj.Method Method)
        When Method.COORDS is used the upper bound of the picture must be included. For example the last coordinate of a 2000x1000 picture is 1500. Then the 2000 must be included as the last index in the array. Otherwise the method can't calculate the values properly.
